						<summary>

						<p><hi rend="bold">Śaka 1305 (1383 A.D.)</hi></p>						

						<p>Registers a gift of 20 cows by <hi rend="bold">Muddarasa,</hi> the minister of <hi rend="bold">Virūpāksha II,</hi> for a perpetual lamp in the temple. Mentions Harihara, the father of the king. The details of the date viz., <hi rend="bold">Śaka 1305 (in words). Rudhirōdgārī, Kārttika, śu. 11, Rēvati, Friday</hi> correspond regularly to <hi rend="bold">A.D. 1383, November 6, Friday, ·44; f.d.n. ·27.</hi></p>						

						</summary>
